reviews.text: Very New York, and I say that as a compliment. Even the staff seem to be mostly Yanks, which means the service is refreshingly welcoming and personable. Wonderful bar.
Chatty bar staff,. Innovative cocktails. Really loved the tequila variation with chili bitters
Perhaps my favorite night hotspot. Classy energy and great vibes overall. You can’t go wrong. The food is also amazing. Usually bring my out of town guests at some point.

With Chope buy-1-get-1-free deal, my cousin and I decided to try out Employees Only on a Saturday evening.

It was relatively quiet when we arrived at 7pm. The restaurant and its bar did get busier and busier as the night unfolded.

We ordered two mains to share. First one is this Sausage Platter, with Chef’s selection of pork, lamb and chicken sausages. I love sausages so much and this heavenly platter gave us a bit of everything! The sausages were all very decent. One of the sausages was filled with cheese (the short one on the right). I particularly love the spicy ones. My cousin is a pickle lover, and she found the cucumbers on the side really good.

Second main we got is this Slow-Cooked Pork Ribs with pickled daikon. The ribs was rightly cooked with a strong BBQ flavour. Meat was tender and easy to cut out from the bone. To our surprise, there was quite a lot of meat! I tried one pickled daikon, and it was really good! No wonder my cousin spoke so highly of the pickled cucumber just now. 

We went on low carbs for this meal unintentionally, but the meat did stuff our tummies with great satisfaction.
Must try their signature Gimlet when you are here! I popped by on a Sunday evening so it has kinda laid back vibe with great music.

result.name: Charcoal HK

reviews.text: The place is very dark, I went there on a rainy day with 3 friends.  Since it stopped raining by the time we arrived, I didn't notice that all the chairs were wet so I sat on it and my short was all wet, it's quite uncomfortable to sit there all night wearing a wet short.  The staff didn't apologise for not putting up those chairs or warn us that those are wet.  Other than that, the service was good, the server recommended an exclusive drink and shisha flavour, which was quite nice.  I enjoyed it despite the incident.
Service is just bad. place very expensive and not worth it. Would not recommend
the worst Shisha bar in Hong Kong. Expensive and definitely not worth it. Bad service attitude.
Great environment and customer service - Barry and team are the absolute nicest!! Definitely my favourite shisha bar in HK :)
The sisha was avarage.I smoke for 15 years. Had to ask to change coal. they charge straight away for the glass one-not even asking. 350 hkd. the view from the terrace not worth. wwould not go again.
